Patch Set 9: Code-Review-1

I am sorry for the really late feedback but I feel it's important. 

I think the original bug [1] for which the logic to set size was added to cache.py doesn't manifest anymore and thus it should be removed.

The original bug [1] happened when an image was added using location and a size of 0 was stored. Now, in v1 [2] & v2 [3] we always fetch the size from the backend and store it with the image. So the case never happens unless..

you have a zero-sized image (empty file), but for that why do we need to set the size back to zero in cache.py ? 

Thus, the right fix is to remove this https://github.com/openstack/glance/blob/master/glance/api/middleware/cache.py#L71

Please tell me if I got something wrong or ping me on IRC for a discussion.

[1] - https://bugs.launchpad.net/glance/+bug/900959
[2] - https://github.com/openstack/glance/blob/master/glance/api/v1/images.py#L816
[3] - https://github.com/openstack/glance/blob/master/glance/location.py#L201
